# Part 3 — coturn, Multi-Region, Bandwidth & DDoS

---

## 7. coturn Global Deployment Model

### 7.1 Regional Topology

```
┌─────────────────── US-EAST (Ashburn) ───────────────────┐
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │         coturn Cluster (K8s DaemonSet)           │   │
│  │                                                    │   │
│  │  ┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐│   │
│  │  │ turn-01 │ │ turn-02 │ │ turn-03 │ │ turn-N  ││   │
│  │  │UDP:3478 │ │UDP:3478 │ │UDP:3478 │ │UDP:3478 ││   │
│  │  │TLS:5349 │ │TLS:5349 │ │TLS:5349 │ │TLS:5349 ││   │
│  │  │ 10Gbps  │ │ 10Gbps  │ │ 10Gbps  │ │ 10Gbps  ││   │
│  │  └─────────┘ └─────────┘ └─────────┘ └─────────┘│   │
│  │                                                    │   │
│  │  Health Monitor ──▶ Prometheus metrics endpoint    │   │
│  │  Allocation Tracker ──▶ Redis (turn:alloc:*)       │   │
│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
│                                                          │
│  NLB (UDP:3478, TCP:5349) ──▶ coturn pod pool           │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
 × 4 regions (US-EAST, EU-WEST, AP-SOUTH, AP-EAST)
```

### 7.2 Sizing Per Region

| Metric | Baseline | Peak |
|--------|----------|------|
| TURN nodes | 20 | 200 |
| Concurrent relayed sessions | 75K | 750K |
| Bandwidth per node | 5 Gbps avg | 10 Gbps cap |
| Instance type | c6gn.2xlarge (8vCPU, 16GB, 25Gbps NW) | — |
| Total regional bandwidth | 100 Gbps | 2 Tbps |

**Why these numbers**: ~15-20% of WebRTC calls require TURN relay. With 3M concurrent calls globally, ~500K need TURN. Distributed across 4 regions = ~125K TURN sessions/region at peak.

### 7.3 Ephemeral TURN Credential Issuance (JWT-bound)

```typescript
import crypto from 'crypto';

const TURN_SECRET = process.env.COTURN_STATIC_AUTH_SECRET!;
const TURN_CREDENTIAL_TTL = 86400; // 24 hours

interface TurnCredentials {
  urls: string[];
  username: string;
  credential: string;
  ttl: number;
}

export function issueTurnCredentials(userId: string, region: string): TurnCredentials {
  const timestamp = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) + TURN_CREDENTIAL_TTL;
  const username = `${timestamp}:${userId}`;
  const credential = crypto
    .createHmac('sha1', TURN_SECRET)
    .update(username)
    .digest('base64');

  const turnDomain = REGION_TURN_MAP[region]; // e.g., 'turn-us.platform.com'

  return {
    urls: [
      `stun:${turnDomain}:3478`,
      `turn:${turnDomain}:3478?transport=udp`,
      `turn:${turnDomain}:3478?transport=tcp`,
      `turns:${turnDomain}:5349?transport=tcp`,
    ],
    username,
    credential,
    ttl: TURN_CREDENTIAL_TTL,
  };
}
```

### 7.4 Geo-Based TURN Selection

```typescript
const REGION_TURN_MAP: Record<string, string> = {
  'us-east': 'turn-use.platform.com',
  'eu-west': 'turn-euw.platform.com',
  'ap-south': 'turn-aps.platform.com',
  'ap-east': 'turn-ape.platform.com',
};

async function selectTurnServer(callerRegion: string, calleeRegion: string): Promise<string> {
  if (callerRegion === calleeRegion) {
    return REGION_TURN_MAP[callerRegion]; // Same region — local TURN
  }

  // Cross-region: select the region with lower current TURN load
  const callerLoad = await redis.get(`turn:load:${callerRegion}`);
  const calleeLoad = await redis.get(`turn:load:${calleeRegion}`);

  // If both are high, consider a neutral region
  if (Number(callerLoad) > 80 && Number(calleeLoad) > 80) {
    return selectLeastLoadedTurn();
  }

  return Number(callerLoad) <= Number(calleeLoad)
    ? REGION_TURN_MAP[callerRegion]
    : REGION_TURN_MAP[calleeRegion];
}
```

### 7.5 TURN Overload Prevention

| Mechanism | Implementation |
|-----------|---------------|
| Per-user bandwidth cap | `max-bps = 2000000` (2 Mbps per allocation) in turnserver.conf |
| Total quota | `total-quota=1000` allocations per node |
| Health-based routing | NLB health check on `/health` (custom HTTP listener); remove unhealthy nodes in <10s |
| Autoscaling trigger | HPA: scale up when `active_allocations / max_allocations > 0.7` |
| Circuit breaker | If all nodes in a region exceed 90% capacity, spill to adjacent region |
| UDP-first optimization | Client ICE agent configured with `iceCandidatePoolSize: 10` and UDP candidates prioritized |

### 7.6 turnserver.conf (Production)

```ini
listening-port=3478
tls-listening-port=5349
min-port=49152
max-port=65535
fingerprint
lt-cred-mech
use-auth-secret
static-auth-secret=${COTURN_STATIC_AUTH_SECRET}
realm=turn.platform.com
total-quota=1000
bps-capacity=0
max-bps=2000000
stale-nonce=600
no-multicast-peers
no-cli
no-tcp-relay
denied-peer-ip=10.0.0.0-10.255.255.255
denied-peer-ip=172.16.0.0-172.31.255.255
denied-peer-ip=192.168.0.0-192.168.255.255
cert=/etc/turn/certs/turn.pem
pkey=/etc/turn/certs/turn.key
cipher-list="ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384:ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256"
prometheus
```

