## 8. Multi-Region Active-Active Strategy

### 8.1 Regional Architecture

```
     ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐
     │   US-EAST   │  │   EU-WEST   │  │   AP-SOUTH  │  │   AP-EAST   │
     │  (Primary)  │  │  (Primary)  │  │  (Primary)  │  │  (Primary)  │
     │             │  │             │  │             │  │             │
     │ WS Gateway  │  │ WS Gateway  │  │ WS Gateway  │  │ WS Gateway  │
     │ Redis Clust │  │ Redis Clust │  │ Redis Clust │  │ Redis Clust │
     │ PostgreSQL  │  │ PostgreSQL  │  │ PostgreSQL  │  │ PostgreSQL  │
     │ Kafka       │  │ Kafka       │  │ Kafka       │  │ Kafka       │
     │ coturn      │  │ coturn      │  │ coturn      │  │ coturn      │
     └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘
            │                │                │                │
            └───────── Kafka MirrorMaker 2 (bidirectional) ────┘
            └───────── CockroachDB / Citus (global SQL) ───────┘
```

### 8.2 Data Consistency Model

| Data Type | Consistency | Replication | Rationale |
|-----------|------------|-------------|-----------|
| Presence (online/offline) | Eventual (200ms) | Kafka compacted topic | Tolerable staleness; high volume |
| Call state machine | Strong (local) | Not replicated cross-region | Call lives in one region's Redis |
| User profiles | Eventual (1s) | CockroachDB multi-region | Read-heavy, write-rare |
| Call history | Eventual (5s) | Async Kafka → regional PG | Append-only, non-critical path |
| Block list | Strong (local) | CockroachDB global table | Security-critical lookups |
| TURN allocations | Local only | Not replicated | Ephemeral, node-bound |

### 8.3 User-to-Region Affinity

```typescript
function determineHomeRegion(user: User): string {
  // Priority: explicit setting > last-login geo > registration geo
  if (user.regionAffinity) return user.regionAffinity;

  const geoRegion = geoip.lookup(user.lastLoginIp)?.region;
  return GEO_TO_REGION_MAP[geoRegion] || 'us-east'; // Default fallback
}
```

