## 9. Global Failover Scenarios

### 9.1 Scenario Matrix

| Scenario | Detection | Response Time | Impact | Recovery |
|----------|-----------|--------------|--------|----------|
| Single WS Gateway pod crash | K8s liveness probe | 10s | Users on that pod reconnect to new pod | Automatic (K8s restart + Redis session intact) |
| Redis shard failure | Sentinel failover | 5-15s | Presence data stale for affected shard | Replica promotion; clients retry |
| Full region outage | Route 53 health check | 30-60s | All users in region disconnected | DNS failover to nearest healthy region |
| TURN cluster overload | Custom metric threshold | 15s | New TURN allocations fail | Spill to adjacent region's TURN |
| Kafka broker failure | ISR shrinkage alert | 10s | Cross-region sync delayed | Automatic broker replacement |
| Network partition (split-brain) | Heartbeat failure detection | 30s | Calls split between partitions | Call auditor reconciliation |

### 9.2 Region Failover: REGION_FAILOVER State

When a full region outage is detected:

```
1. Route 53 marks region unhealthy (health check fails 3x)
2. DNS TTL (30s) expires; traffic routes to nearest healthy region
3. Clients reconnect to new region via WebSocket
4. On reconnect, gateway checks Redis for active calls:
   a. If user was in CONNECTED state → transition to REGION_FAILOVER
   b. Notify peer: "partner's region failed, maintaining call via TURN"
   c. ICE restart with new TURN credentials from healthy region
   d. If ICE restart succeeds → back to CONNECTED
   e. If fails within 30s → FAILED
5. Presence keys expired from old region; rebuilt in new region
```

### 9.3 Sudden Spike: 1M Calls in <60 Seconds

```
Detection: Custom metric (call_initiations_per_second) exceeds 16K/s
Response:
  1. HPA triggers immediate scale-up of WS Gateway pods (target: 10x baseline)
  2. TURN cluster HPA triggers (pre-configured to handle 5x baseline)
  3. Redis Cluster: no scaling needed (pre-provisioned for 10x)
  4. Circuit breaker activates at 20K calls/s per region:
     - New call initiations are queued (not rejected)
     - Queue drain rate: 5K/s per region
     - Client receives CALL_QUEUED status with ETA
  5. If sustained >5 minutes: alert on-call SRE
```

