## 10. Bandwidth Cost Optimization

### 10.1 Cost Model

| Path | Bandwidth Cost | % of Calls |
|------|---------------|-----------|
| P2P direct (STUN only) | $0 (client bandwidth) | ~50% |
| P2P through NAT (STUN) | $0 (client bandwidth) | ~30% |
| TURN relay (UDP) | $0.02/GB (cloud egress) | ~15% |
| TURN relay (TCP/TLS) | $0.02/GB (cloud egress) | ~5% |

### 10.2 Optimization Strategies

| Strategy | Savings | Implementation |
|----------|---------|----------------|
| UDP-first ICE | 40% TURN cost reduction | Client-side `iceTransportPolicy: 'all'` with UDP candidates prioritized |
| Adaptive bitrate | 30% bandwidth reduction | Sender-side bandwidth estimation via REMB/TWCC |
| TURN allocation pooling | 15% cost reduction | Pre-warm TURN allocations; reuse across ICE restarts |
| Regional TURN selection | 25% egress reduction | Route TURN traffic to same-region relay |
| Audio-only fallback | 80% bandwidth reduction | Auto-switch to audio when bandwidth <200kbps |
| Codec optimization | 20% bandwidth reduction | Prefer VP9/AV1 over VP8; Opus for audio |
| Short-call optimization | 10% cost reduction | Skip TURN for calls <5s (missed/rejected) |

### 10.3 Monthly Cost Projection at Scale

| Component | Cost/Month |
|-----------|-----------|
| TURN bandwidth (500K concurrent × 500kbps avg × 30% TURN) | ~$180K |
| coturn compute (800 c6gn.2xlarge across 4 regions) | ~$450K |
| WS Gateway compute (2000 pods across 4 regions) | ~$300K |
| Redis Cluster (24 r6g.2xlarge across 4 regions) | ~$85K |
| Kafka (cross-region replication) | ~$60K |
| PostgreSQL / CockroachDB | ~$40K |
| Observability stack | ~$50K |
| **Total infrastructure** | **~$1.17M/month** |

