## 11. DDoS Protection Strategy

### 11.1 Multi-Layer Defense

```
Layer 3/4 (Volumetric)
  ├── AWS Shield Advanced / Cloud Armor (10 Tbps absorption)
  ├── Anycast-distributed edge absorbs attack traffic locally
  └── Auto-mitigation: <10s detection, <30s full mitigation

Layer 7 (Application)
  ├── WebSocket handshake rate limiting (100/s per IP)
  ├── JWT validation at connection time (reject unauthenticated)
  ├── Per-socket message rate limiting:
  │     call:initiate → 1 per 5s per user
  │     webrtc:offer → 1 per 10s per call
  │     ice-candidate → 50 per 30s per call
  │     heartbeat → 1 per 25s per socket
  ├── Payload size limits (SDP: 10KB max, ICE: 1KB max)
  └── IP reputation scoring (Redis sorted set, exponential decay)

TURN Layer
  ├── Authentication required (no anonymous allocations)
  ├── Per-user allocation limits (max 2 concurrent)
  ├── Bandwidth caps per allocation (2 Mbps)
  ├── denied-peer-ip for private ranges (prevent SSRF)
  └── Short credential TTL (24h) with rotation
```

### 11.2 IP Reputation Engine

```typescript
async function updateIpReputation(ip: string, event: 'CONNECT' | 'AUTH_FAIL' | 'RATE_LIMIT' | 'ABUSE') {
  const penalties: Record<string, number> = {
    CONNECT: 0,
    AUTH_FAIL: 10,
    RATE_LIMIT: 25,
    ABUSE: 100,
  };

  const score = await redis.zincrby('ip:reputation', penalties[event], ip);
  await redis.expire('ip:reputation', 86400); // 24h rolling window

  if (Number(score) > 500) {
    // Add to block list for 1 hour
    await redis.set(`ip:blocked:${ip}`, '1', 'EX', 3600);
    logger.warn({ ip, score }, 'IP blocked due to reputation score');
  }
}
```

